criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Hospital admission for SLE-related issue;

          2. clinical diagnosis of systemic lupus erythematosus (SLE) from a physician;

          3. 18 years of age or older;

          4. able to provide informed consent and take part in ongoing assessment/evaluation
             activities (self-reported questionnaires);

          5. able to commit to duration of study (3 months);

          6. able to communicate in English; and

          7. have an active phone line (landline or cell phone) for the duration of the study, if
             agreeing to phone sessions with the lay patient navigator/care coordinator.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. cognitive impairment;

          2. acute decompensation of chronic conditions precluding participation;

          3. conditions that preclude participation in assessments (e.g. blindness or deafness);
             and

          4. terminal illness or life expectancy less than 6 months as evaluated by physician.
